Package: SNACR
Title: Analyze Multi-Domain Data Using Two-Step Component and Network Analysis
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
  person("Pia", "Tio", , "piatio@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8984-491X")),
  person("Katrijn", "Van Deun", , "K.VanDeun@uvt.nl", role = "aut"),
  person("Lourens", "Waldorp", , "L.J.Waldorp@uva.nl", role = "aut"))
Description: A two-step analysis of multi-domain/block/source data sets to estimate cross-domain partial correlations. 
    In step one, component analysis splits data set's variance in domain-specific and cross-domain/common components. 
    In step two, network analysis estimates (partial) correlations of the cross-domain/common component. 
